caption: Best food, super friendly staff, regularly excellent mood. They charge affordable rates and the food quality is good. Fantastic work.

The pizza tastes good but the people making the pizzas masks were not on correctly with their noses exposed... it was our first time trying this place. The price is similar to most pizza places in the area. We got the NY style pizza and it was reminiscent of NY style pizza.

One of the most special places I've ever visited. Discovered this place in early 2019 and have come back for amazing pinball, beer and pizza more times than I can count. The quality and care put into this place is unmatched, a really fun place and massive breath of fresh air for Bethesda.
Real NY pizza. So good.
Came for the pinball, can't rate the food because I had eaten already.
Fantastic pizza and pinball.  Closest thing to New York style pizza I found so far. Plus a great selection of pinball machines - only 50 cents per game!
username: Angry Gherkin Vintage Goods by Pheff

caption: Very delicious!
The pizza here is fantastic. I’ve lived in the area for years and nothing compares in terms of price and quality. If you like New York style pizza - this is definitely worth trying.

The most fun place in Bethesda, without question, and an unmissable attraction. The pizza is great--the white pizza is actually some of the best I've ever had, perfectly balanced, cooked, and richly flavorful. The selection of sodas is also great, and I have VUK to thank for introducing me to Reed's Ginger Beer. Of course, the pinball machines are the highlight of any trip here. There's a great selection and they're all immaculately well maintained in my experience. Great service--the people manning the counter are always personable and chill. And overall, there's a fantastic metal aesthetic to the whole place. Probably the coolest little joint in Bethesda. If you haven't been, you're missing out!

Recommend this pizza place.  Good food, great prices and staff is good.  Plenty of choices not he menu to satisfy different preferences.  When this place is open for inside seating the pinball machines are classic.  Great vibe and good food.
Incredible pizza in a cool environment
Take out takes forever

It's a fun atmosphere for people of all ages, the food is great and quickly served, on several occasions I've had the chance to talk to one of the employees (Michel) great guy and very helpful, when you visit ask for Michel.
Had a great night out with friends the pepperoni pizza 🍕🤤was delicious Michele was very nice and provided good service will be eat here more often
Great atmosphere! Awesome pizza as well! The employee Michele is awesome!! Great guy always has great a attitude 10/10 would recommend

How is this place always dead??? Best pizza in Bethesda and seems like it’s always dead. Hector is the NICEST employee. Always a nice conversation and great customer service!
Get the deep dish Sicilian with pepperoni and you can’t go wrong 💛🍕🍕

I've gone here twice now and both times I've had an excellent time with nice staff, great pizza, and fun machines. Hope this place stays around Bethesda for years to come because sadly there's nothing quite like it around here!
Great pizza and some fun pinball

Wow, I am so impressed!! I’m giving 5 stars because I’ve been craving a New York style pizza for a while down here in DC/Maryland,  and these guys know what they are doing. The pizza is the best in town. Better than anyone in a 30-50 mile radius, They got the best tasting pizza in the area, And best tasting pizzas EVER!! Omg, like no joke, but besides that, they also serve ice cold BEER!! This place is the BEST!!  My first time coming in i was hesitant because it seemed a little dark inside, and not much of an atmosphere on the outside, but after walking through the cool place, and meeting Hector(the best pizzaiolo in town by the way), I felt great, and also taken care of. He told me the history about the place and he was also friendly and very dedicated to his work. Hector also speaks highly of the owner which makes me think they have a great understanding of eachother, and that’s what makes good employees and owners make the best out of a business. It was just awesome customer service in my opinion, and the whole time he was talking to me, he kept on making pizzas at the same time. This dude is awesome!! Talk about multitasking. Wow!! But, besides the great service and the amazing pizzas(that are always available by the slice by the way....genius!!!) they also have pin ball machines!!!! Yes, I said it, actual pinball machines and old school arcade stuff. I’m not into that kind of stuff, but I found it to be a great extra touch besides the good food and service. I love you guys!! Great place!! Great food!! Great atmosphere!!

This place is a family friendly place, games for kids to play, kids loved the pizza. Hector was very nice and attentive of our table with pizza and drinks.We had a great time there! I definitely would be going back !
I regularly stop buying some food here. I enjoy the prompt customer service and well cooked food. Kudos.
Great pizza
The pizza was reallu good! Also the atmosphere is really chill and nostalgic. They have an awesome collection of pinball machines and its a fun experience.
Fresh pizza, cold beer, and fun pinball machines!
Nice
Real quarters and only about .50 per play. Pizza is good, beer is good, love this place. I want to buy an Iron Maiden Pinball machine now
Awesome spot... well maintained pinball machines and some delicious pizza!
I love this place it’s so fun there everything is great pinball and NY pizza I can’t wait to go there again good job guys

The pizza is amazing here.  The crust is perfect, the sauce is perfect, the amount of cheese is perfect. Everything is perfect.  What pushes this place above and beyond however, is the customer service. I had an issue with my Grubhub order, and Hector helped make it right. He's awesome.
Great staff with a good attitude. The pizza is incredibly delicious! It is a nice, welcoming and clean establishment. The pinball games are fantastic and quite addicting lol.
Great pizza, and tons of fun pinball machines
Love going to this place the pizza is great and my favorite game is the older machine in the back
The place is the best Great tile for all ages!
Awesome pinball and good pizza. Love this place. Also the beer is more affordable than a bar.

This was my first time there, and I've found a new local favorite that I'm bringing my family back to! It's a cool little place with a wall stacked with pinball machines. Kinda of an old-school vibe throughout the place, like your favorite local pizza place from 20 or 30nyears ago. Anyway, the place is pretty cool. So I had to try the pizza. And it was delicious! If you like NY style, you have to try this pizza! It's making my mouth water just thinking about it! I'll be back!
Amazing pizza! Amazing pinball, and they have beer!

I'm a fan of this place. .50 cent pinball and a slice of pizza is a great way to get away during work. The pizza is premade and it takes about 2 minutes for it to go from oven to my mouth. I'm crazy busy so it's awesome to get something quick and tasty.
This place is perfect of you want an easy, fun and chill night out. The pizza is excellent too
Such a fun place! Great pizza and plenty of pin ball machines to keep smiles going.
Good pizza. Good machines. Good hangout for kids. And their parents.

Ahh, Pizza and Pinball, what a combo.  This place is small, the tables can be wobbly, and they're closed Mondays. But in spite of that, it's a great place to grab a slice of good pizza and play pinball on the variety of machines they have there. For a pinball and pizza joint, I give it 5 stars. The pizza is way better than you might expect, and I believe it's some of the best in Bethesda.
Good pizza and great pinball
Rico makes the best pizza n a great atmosphere.

NY style pizza and tons of pinball machines!!! Super friendly staff. I love it!! The slices are big and the crust is lite and a just a tiny bit crisp - real nice! I’m getting a kick out of all the kids playing pinball. Bells ringing, lights flashing! It’s a great environment. And they have some outdoor seating in a little private courtyard so that’s a bonus. This place is great!!  However, apparently Bethesda charges for parking after 6PM with no real clear signage for us folks from out of town. I have a $45 ticket as a result. So put some money in that meter!!
Fun!!! No frills, just basic old fashioned good pinball in a superrelaxed atmosphere, love it
Local gem for sure!!  Pizza was amazing
1st time meeting Mike and he was very nice to me and the kids. Very tentative, understand my complicated order and kind. I will be returning and the kids enjoyed him.
Bad actitud with customers and deliveries,  they take a lot time preparing the orders.
Great pizza, great posters, great pinball. Perfect after class spot
Pizza was on point. Good service. Rare place kids Will be entertained long enough for adults to have a brew or 2 and chill... The death metal theme is pretty aggressive though.
Great pizza and pinballs, great for the whole family as long as the family likes pinball

I was really excited to try this place. My partner and I arrived on 11/8 between 8-10pm to give it a shot. Upon considering the menu, I witnessed a black gentlemen who was making a large pizza on the counter have a phlegmy coughing fit onto the pizza he was making as well as the open case of prepared pizza sitting under the heat lamp. I heard someone say, "that does not sound good" to which he replied "Nope, it don't!" as he continued on preparing the pizza... Needless to say my partner and I left the establishment shortly thereafter never to return. I don't know what kind of toxic environment the VUK management maintains there, but apparently the employees are so miserable with their jobs here that they really could not care less about the job, the workplace, or making the customers seriously ill. The employee exuded a total disregard and reprehensible lack of care for any sanitation concerns. If this is what they are doing in perfect view of customers, I can only imagine what goes on here when no one is looking. I could not in good conscience order from this place nor recommend it to anyone.

Best New York-style pizza in Bethesda.  But it's a pinball place!  So get it to go (or use an app to get delivery if you're patient).  Pizzas are one size -- enormous -- and the cheese pizza is only $14.  Tastes great when you're eating it, but must be salty because I'm thirsty afterward (more than usual for pizza).  Love it!

Edit: Wanted to update to say that this place was a lifesaver for us as a last minute venue for my kids birthday party, when our original plan got rained out. The owner opened an hour early for us, and the children and adults alike all had an amazing time.  Great pizza, beer, soda and $0.50 pinball games. Kid friendly during the day

Fun spot for pinball and beer. Can't say anything about the food.  I wish there were better vegan options. I'd happily give them 5 stars if they had a decent dairy-free pie or carried some plant-based meats. With &Pizza and a few other joints around, it makes it hard to go here for the pizza. But the pinball collection is great and it's nice to have a value-priced beer while you're there.
Pizza is very good and the pinball machines just make it better. The value for pizza is very good but the toppings and cheese amount should be increased. It was very spare and dry.
Great location for Pinball ! Food is ok and very cheap ! Nice outdoor seating .
Fun to spend an hour here. Easy to find parking and a good idea if you don't want to spend a lot of money and feel a little nostalgic. Good food, a selection of pizza and soft serve.
Great games & delish pizza.
My kids have never played pinball and they had a fabulous time! We had to keep going back for more pizza. Should've bought a whole pie.
Great pizza, great pinball machines!
My son and I love to come and play pinball. Old school and fun. Plus a great hot slice of pizza is icing on the cake.

Disgusting place. Some of the worst pizza I've ever had. I was most put off by the fact the cashier used his dirty bare hands to pull apart the pizza slice to put into the oven. The health inspector should come investigate!
Amazing pizza. Great selection of pinball machines. Good soft serve, too. Definitely a great addition to Bethesda's food scene.
They have good pizza.
Delicious pizza!
Amazing pizza, great pinball, great customer service

It's a great addition to the area, we love Pizza by the slice! Something for everyone's taste and all very yummy. If you like a New York style thin folding it in half 🍕 and Pinball machines this is the spot!

Great collection of pinball machines, the most I've seen in a while. 8 or 9 contemporary ones, one 1970's vintage model, and a couple of video games, at the time of this writing. I wouldn't go there just for the pizza, but it is acceptable. What seems a bit of a hole in the wall at first is actually a hidden treasure for pinball enthusiasts. Thanks to the owner of Mom's Organic Market for having the vision and passion to open and support this place.
Pizza was only okay.
Best local spot in MoCo for pizza that’s not a chain restaurant, great pinball & not too loud/busy (depending on when you go). There is an outdoor patio that is shaded. They have free coffee 😊
Cool little place. Not much space, but they got some really cool pinball machines. Didn't get to try the pizza, but it looked good. It is a small place so it can get tight.
This place is a blast from the past. I had a great time playing pinball! Also the pizza was excellent NY style pizza.
VÜK has great vibes, solid pizza, and even has free coffee. What more can you ask for??
The pizza by the slice was meh, but the vibe was cool. Pinball machines all worked. A fun place to hang.
Awesome - great games rotated regularly, good pizza, good beer. Super fun.
By the pie or by the slice,,,,Great Pizza at a Great price. Pinballs Rule.
Good pizza and pinball. I'll go back again
Pizza, beer, and pinball. Truth in advertising.

This is a judgemental star because I stood in front of this establishment and peaked in, but didn't enter because it didn't look too inviting. This place is so tiny, I passed by it twice before locating it. First, I drove pass it in the car, and later parked after I couldn't spot it. Next, I walked right pass it while trying to find it on foot before discovering the address. It didn't have a whole bunch of pinball machines like I imagined upon Iooking through the window. I saw about 8 , but there could be more. I never went in to try the pizza.
Great Pizza.  Games are in the best shape.  Amazing collection.
Great pizza (and this is coming from a New Yorker)! Nice selection of pinball machines and classic arcade games. I only wish that I had some more time and some more quarters.
Great pizza and pinball!
Pizza is truly New York style, the place also has a retro feel.
Not sure about the pizza. Great destination for pinball fanatics. Just stopped for rain and played for a bit.

Do not pass on this place! Great place to hang, play a few rounds of pinball (or hours with like me lol), and you have to get a slice of pizza...so good! The folks who visit this place are pretty cool too! Everyone is always so nice and everyone is just there to have some fun!! Scott, the owner, collects pinball machines (pretty awesome ones I might add!) and I'm happy to report his habit supports my Sunday habit of playing pinball!

Must just be a bad day. Pinball cool but they just told us 1 1/2 hours for a slice. One worker just cursed out a customer and the workers are  grabbing the food and toppings with their bare hands and alternatly wiping sweat from their forehead. Not that busy at all either. Employees super grumpy and filthy.  I have watched 4 other customers walk out in last 10 minutes mumbling. Really disgusting kitchen adds to charm. Pinball cool for 2 stars Reviews say pizza good. Will never find out

Amazing crust on the pizza.  Very tasty.  The tomatoe sause is flavorful.  Other ingredients are premium.  They have a good soft-serve ice cream.  My kids love the pinball machines. They are not very good so can eat through a lot of quarters. The games fill much of the resteraunt so there is limited seating.   The machines fill the place with lots of noise.
Pizza was great... Love the pins!!!
Punk rock pizza and beer joint with pinball tournaments. What is not to love?
I like vuk alot
Good pinball
Great pizza and even better pinball
Perfect Patio & Pinball weather
It's great! They have pinball, pizza and ice cream, what more could you want!
Fun for everyone!
Good pizza and great pinball.
Awesome place, great pinball machines great pizza and great pricing on beer
pizza was yummy. $3 pizza, 50¢ pinball, and free coffee. Honestly not sure how this place manages to pay rent in Bethesda. Also, the bathroom was surprisingly nice!

I walked in and heard "Seek and Destroy" by Metallica playing, so I knew I was in a rad place. Pizza is delicious and affordable. Bring your quarters and play pinball ALL day! The Iron Maiden machine is the best one. Try to beat my high score of 80 million, I dare you.
Great pizza and nostalgia!
Pinball, pizza and beer

Some of the best pizza in Montgomery County. Really does taste like New York York pizza,  although not as greasy, which I think is a positive. Also has about a dozen pinball machines, which is pretty awesome, although they make it a noisy place. Not the place to go if looking for a quiet place. Highly recommended for its pizza. Not to be missed.
Great atmosphere and vibe. Fun place to take the kids for pizza, Pinball and video games.
They have great arcade games, and the pizza is amazing!! Perfect for an afternoon with friends.

I've played pinball before but that, pizza and the overall chill atmosphere of the place really makes the experience. Definitely a cool hangout spot on par with a roller rink; the classics never get old!
Crust was soggy and we had to wait after call in
Only went in there for the pinball machines which are quite old and not calibrated.
Dope place to chill  and catch some vibes
Good pizza, great drink selection, pinball machines, soft serve, friendly staff, clean facility. We gathered for a friend's birthday and had a great time.

Retro, geeky, delicious, cheap, kid friendly, good service. This place is amazing.  They have step stools for children, a pinball leader board, and a cool decor. I just wish my 3 year old was a touch older so she'd appreciate the games a little bit more and stay longer.... We both loved the pizza so it worked out just fine!  The St Elmo parking garage was across the street so getting in and out was easy as Bethesda can be.
Great NYC style pizza.
Good pinball bar! Only wish they had even more machines!
Pizza and ice cream are great!  Best selection of pinball machines around!

I love coming here. They rotate their pinball machines so you'll see new stuff every few weeks. The pizza is good too and the beer selection is fair for a small spot. My favorite pinball machine is the creature from the black lagoon

A great place to visit if you're in the mood to revisit the 80s. Has both vintage and modern pin ball machines as well as arcade game simulators. The pizza is great and the place is always super clean. The staff are super cool. A parking garage is conveniently located across the street.
Tiny space, but otherwise a cool place for pizza, beer, and pinball.
Awesome spot !
Pinball was as excellent as the Pizza
Nice cozy place to go for some good pizza and play a few classic pinball games. Thin crust NY style 🍕!!!!

Amazing pizza- The best NY-style pizza I've come across in the DC area, and I've probably tried every other alternative. Thin crust, large slices, great taste and great prices. The pinball machines are cool too

33 years on this Earth, and I've never managed to completely sate my hunger for pizza. That is, until Vük. 2 slices of Neapolitan-style thin crust and 3 toppings-loaded Sicilian slices later, I had reached peak pizza. I regret nothing, except for the four bites I left behind.
I ordered a pizza, had no cheese and topping on the outer part only the middle.
Pizza is delicious and games are plentiful. Great fun family afternoon
Great food, a lot of pinball machines. Relaxed atmosphere.
Fantastic Pizza. Really cool atmosphere in here.  Crew is cool too. I will frequent this place.
Good Pizza..Great Pin-Ball..cool spot
So awesome to play pinball. 50 cents a game.what a neat find in Bethesda.
Love this place.  Decent pizza and great pinball machines.
(Translated by Google) Good.  (Original) Bom.
Fun pinball tables and classic arcade games.
Great pinball, beer, and pizza.  Probably the best pizza in Bethesda.  You do have to turn your back on a weeping angel to get change though.  Yikes!
Decent pizza.  Strange sodas.  Great pinball.
Great pizza and great pinball.  Pinball is the focus here, but pizza is worth the trip on it's own.  Fresh-made dough is often in the mixer in the back.
So fun. Best place anywhere
Love the pinball. Not crazy about the pizza - go to Corner Slice down the street.
Pizza by the slice and pinball, it does not get any better.

Great pinball.  Top notch games.  Pizza is also very good.  Decent local bottle selection for ~$4 a bottle. Can get crowded when the pinball league is running (Sunday evenings).  Closed on Mondays.  Outdoor seating available.
Best pizza in Bethesda hands down, and a fun atmosphere for pinball enthusiasts.
Great place, great pizza, large slices, staff is very accommodating. Definitely recommend!
Love this place.... best staff, great pizza and pinballl.... plus Crazy Climber, Mr Do and Yie-Ar Kung Fu!

The pinball machines are all in great condition. The pizza is great. Casual players should call ahead of time to make sure to avoid league meetings because the machines get quite crowded at those times. This place is EVERYTHING it should be.
Good pizza, great pinball. Gets a bit overrun with little ones at times, but they gotta pay their bills somehow...

Never have I ever thought that I would want to play pinball and eat delicious pizza at the same time, but VUK makes it possible, and does with with perfect execution!  My slice of the supreme pizza (pepperoni, sausage, onions, and mushrooms) was delicious. The crust was crispy but also doughy, and everything was heated all the way through. This was already my second dinner so I was pushing it a bit, hence why I didn't try the soft swirl too. Next time!  They have around 10 pinball machines inside, ranging from the "old school" to newer ones like The Hobbit that looked pretty fancy and new with all it's digitized screens. It cost $0.50 for a game, and if you put in $1 and push "Start" twice, you get to play the 2-player mode. The guy behind the counter can help you exchange dollar bills for coins which was convenient.  So much fun! I love that this exists in Bethesda and I'll be coming back soon!

Perfect place for a slice and some pinball. A perfect rainy day lunch activity with the kids. A nice variety of machines which all are quarter fed, some multi classic game arcade machines in the back.
Pizza is amazing and the staff is super friendly.
Pinball, tasty pizza and beer! It's a small place with the emphasis on pizza and pinball, there is not much indoor seating for eating but a nice patio it back. Go check it out!

This is a journey back in time to Shakeys pizza parlor. The pizza is excellent and the bonus pinball many of them for 50 cents a game. Try all the new pins from Dialed In to Galaxy of the Gardians. They serve soft serve Ice Cream as well and Dr Browns sodas. It is a lot of fun. Spend a hour hear tale your children show them what once was so many venues.

Great place to relive childhood arcade memories.  Small game room has 10-12 pinball machines dating from 1977 to new. Cost is reasonable at 50 cents per play.  My review does not include the pizza.  We only played games.

A pinball joint is a rarity today. My 7 year old son loves to come and play this old school game, and it keeps that connection to the past. This isn't some massive arcade place. About a dozen pinball machines and a few old arcade classics. It doesn't hurt that it's right next to my friend Chef Tony's awesome restaurant.

The pizza here is spectacular! Competes well with the pizza I’ve had in NYC  There’s a great selection of pinball machines that’ll keep you busy for hours. There’s even an arcade machine with classics like DK and Tetris
A more affordable version of Dave & Busters. The pinball games are fun to play, The pizza is good, and you get Free Coffee! I would have this be my regular place to hang out with my friends!
If you haven't been here for lunch you are not living right.

This place was awesome. I really had no expectations other than I knew they had pinball. When we went and ordered two slices of pepperoni the guy behind the counter made a fresh pepperoni pizza instead of heating up the old slices. While we waited we were able to play a bunch of different pinball machines which may be the greatest way to wait for food. The pizza crust was absolutely amazing, the sauce was perfectly flavored, and there were a lot of crispy toppings. My only real drawback is that for $3.50 a slice I would have expected the slice to be a bit bigger, I mean for $7 for two slices I could take that money to any of the other great pizza places in Bethesda and be about half of the cost of a 16" one topping pizza ($16 at M&N or $11 at Vace).
Great staff , pizza and a lot of pinballs in good condition.
Great pinball selection. Machines well maintained.
Unbelievably kind staff.
Pinball and pizza! What else could you want? Pizza is ok, but pinball makes up for it!

As pinball goes this place is amazing. You couldn't ask for a better lineup of machines in perfect working condition. Unfortunately it took over an hour to get two pizzas on the table. Even more unfortunate that the pizza isn't that great. Come for the pinball and maybe a beer, skip the pizza and eat somewhere else before or after.
Had a great time here.  Awesome pinball, great atmosphere, tasty pizza!

A great laid-back pizza parlor. I love playing pinball and this is one of the  best places to play! Games are in great condition and most are recent. I just wish that I lived closer. I don't eat the pizza, but my friends tell me it's great - and they give huge slices. I am trying to get them to offer cut up raw veggies but I haven't been successful at doing that. Staff (often just one person) are great also.

Gem of a pizza place. Not a huge selection of food or pizza types, but that's not really the point. Fun casual atmosphere with a great variety of pinball games. Prices seemed reasonable, especially in Bethesda.
Pizza and pinball, what's not to like?
Old School Pinball prices and machines. The beer is cold and the Pizza is as good as a New York slice. I would hang  out here and it would be all good. I would even just chill with my friends.
Pinball machines and a few video games.
Love this place. Ready to go pizza options, a few beer choices, LOTS of pinball options. Great chill place for relaxing with a small (2-6) group of friends.
Pinball and New York style pizza. That's a winning combination.

If you like pinball, this is the place in Bethesda. They have about a dozen well-maintained machines, 3 ball, 50 cents a game. Age range from absolutely brand new (Jersey Jack Pinball company) to pre-digital (one machine). The pizza is pretty good as well, and there are sometimes more people eating pizza than playing pinball. on the week night I visited only a dozen people played any pinball over the 3 hours I was there.
Great NY style pizza and tons of pinball machines and arcade games that are only ¢50/play. Awesome and unique spot. Def worth a visit.
Basic pizza menu, but tasty and warmed when ordered. Bring plenty of quarters because the pinball machines is where it's at!

So the best thing here is the pinball. They have a great lineup of machines including some 2015/16 releases. The pizza is passable, but nothing special. The staff are always friendly too. Overall though the place is fun. It hearkens back to the 80's and you can totally recreate your twelfth birthday party here.

Excellent NY style pizza, and amazing soft serve ice cream.  I love going here for a pie, and playing a few games of pinball while I wait.  If you're OK with not having a million toppings to choose from, this place is worth a shot.  The staff and owners are great.
Great pinball machines and pizzas. Pinballs are in mint condition. What a treat for the whole family.
Great spot, laid back pizza joint with a bunch pinball games.  Staff is awesome.
Best NY style pizza place in Bethesda.  The quality of the slices varies sometimes but lately has been pretty even keel.  Lots of pinball machines as well.
Great pizza and pinball!
SO EPIC
Anything with this amount of pinball gets 5 stars, period. Good pizza, beer, 50 cents a game pinball. All the machines I played work great.
If you like pinball machines this is the place!
Decent pizza by the slice, but the real draw is the great selection of pinball machines.
Fun place
Great prices on beer and food, lots of character, very geek-oriented

most legit nyc pizza in the area.  inside is narrow and usually crowded with pinball players.  if you're there just for pizza go in through the outside patio to go right to the counter.  also best soft serve of all time.
A myriad of pinball machines in an old school vintage atmosphere. The pizza is delicious NY style.
Pizza is very good. Honest. Plenty of pinball machines. Jukebox is loud. Great stuff.
Can't say... We waited 10 minutes and no one paid attention or came to ask if we want anything...
Nice little place with a lot of pinball machines and pizza.
Great pizza.

Some friends and I checked out VÜK on Saturday, May 21st and we had a great time.  The pinball games are all in fine shape and work well, and there's a good selection of them.  There are also two multi-game video arcade cabinets, including a multi-Williams with other games on it too, including some I had never seen before.  The pins all seemed to be 50 cents a play (with a discount if you buy a lot of credits at once) and the multi-williams was two plays for 50 cents. The controls on the multi were a bit hinky I thought, but it was still fun.  There was a big screen TV showing a movie and good rock music on the audio system in the place, including classic Pink Floyd.  I approve!  It was good to see families and people of all ages enjoying pinball. I enjoyed the slice of mushroom and onion pizza I tried. Overall, it was several hours of fun in downtown Bethesda for about five bucks. The staff were also friendly and helpful. Check this place out if you like pinball and hopefully they'll relocate and keep going when their lease is up in 2018.
